'''Moving the yardsticks''' is a common expression which means "making progress" and is used in political and corporate venues to express proactive actions. The phrase originates from [[American football]], where every ten yards of forward progress by the [[Offense (sports)|offense]] moves the [[yardstick]]s ahead to measure the next ten yards of progress.

This expression is not to be confused with "moving the goalposts", also derived from American football, which means to make a set of goals more difficult just as they are being met.

